In simulations \emph{asp\_2} and \emph{asp\_3}, corresponding to the values of $H/R=0.02$ and $H/R=0.05$, respectively, we do not see any effects of the forced compression because all mass is swallowed before it could be squeezed by the secondary, due to the increased viscosity. 

